               <msContents>
                  <summary>Christian prayer of petition concerning the prudence of a journey and the likelihood of success. Grenfell and Hunt, comparing it to pagan counterparts P.Oxy. 923 and P.Fay. 137, suppose that it would have been deposited in a church.</summary>
                  <msItemStruct>
                     <note type="general">7 lines written with the fibers</note>
                     <note type="general">Legible Byzantine cursive hand</note>
                     <note type="general">Text runs flush to all four edges</note>
                     <note type="general">6 nomina sacra: God (l. 1), father (l. 3), lord (l. 3), savior (l. 3), Jesus (l. 4), Christ (l. 4)</note>
                     <note type="general">No script on verso</note>
                     <note type="local_note">Pap. 2, Special Collections, Luce Library, Princeton Theological Seminary, Princeton, N.J.</note>
